As of the census<ref name="census2">{{cite web |title=U.S. Census website |url=https://www.census.gov |accessdate=May 23, 2011 |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref> of 2010, there were 191 people living in the CDP. There were 123 housing units. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|racial makeup]] of the town was 95.3% White, 2.6% American Indian and Alaska Native, 1.0% Asian, 0.5% Native Hawaiian and Other Pacific Islander, and 0.5% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 1.6% of the population.

